olive oil
1 cucumber
1 carrot
1 packet pork mince
2 tsp soy sauce
½ packet hoisin sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar
1 packet onion & garlic paste

• Slice cucumber into thin sticks. Grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook pork mince and onion & garlic paste, breaking up
with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add the soy sauce and hoisin sauce (see ingredients) and cook until
combined, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts,
until warmed through.
• In a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, garlic aioli, a drizzle of
rice wine vinegar and a pinch of salt.

• To serve, fill tortillas with slaw, Vietnamese-style pork, carrot and cucumber.
Enjoy!